Ow.

08:47.236 --> 08:49.530
<i>Another day and
another round of violence</i>

08:49.614 --> 08:51.657
<i>in Syria on Saturday.</i>

08:51.741 --> 08:54.577
<i>Fighting in the northern city
of Atma has raged for days</i>

08:54.660 --> 08:57.538
<i>causing widespread destruction
and casualties that have now</i>

08:57.622 --> 09:01.459
<i>topped 35,000,
with many of those civilians.</i>

09:01.542 --> 09:03.586
<i>The addition of more troops
in what are sure to be</i>

09:03.669 --> 09:06.505
<i>even bloodier battles ahead
has fueled worries</i>

09:06.589 --> 09:10.551
<i>within the rebel ranks
and around the world.</i>

09:10.635 --> 09:13.679
<i>Talks in Washington calling
for the arming of insurgents</i>

09:13.763 --> 09:15.890
<i>in Syria.</i>

09:15.973 --> 09:18.267
<i>We should start
considering all options,</i>

09:18.351 --> 09:20.436
<i>including arming
the opposition.</i>

09:20.519 --> 09:22.730
<i>Experts say
arming the fighting groups</i>

09:22.813 --> 09:24.690
<i>among the opposition
is a sure way</i>

09:24.774 --> 09:27.902
<i>to drag the country
into a protracted civil war.</i>

09:27.985 --> 09:29.987
<i>It will also
further marginalize</i>

09:30.071 --> 09:33.157
<i>those in the opposition who
have advocated non-violence</i>

09:33.241 --> 09:35.243
<i>or to advance
political strategy.</i>

11:23.184 --> 11:26.187
<i>Please leave a
message after the beep.</i>

11:26.270 --> 11:28.814
<i>Hey, Dad, it's Chris-
Did you get' him?</i>

11:28.939 --> 11:31.776
<i>No, I go! the machine.
Why don't you fry his cell?</i>

11:31.859 --> 11:34.612
<i>'Cause he doesn't have a cell.
You could email him.</i>

11:34.695 --> 11:37.281
<i>Or a computer.</i>

11:37.365 --> 11:39.742
<i>So I'll just leave a message-</i>

11:39.825 --> 11:41.660
Hey, buddy.
How's it going?

11:41.744 --> 11:45.081
Hey. It's good.
It's great.

11:45.164 --> 11:48.125
How about you? You been
radio silent for a while.

11:48.209 --> 11:50.336
Just, you know,
keeping busy.

11:50.419 --> 11:53.047
As usual.

11:53.130 --> 11:54.757
<i>So, hey, listen.</i>

11:54.840 --> 11:56.425
<i>I don't know
if you saw the invite,</i>

11:56.509 --> 11:58.719
<i>but tomorrow's
Matthew's baptism.</i>

11:58.803 --> 12:00.930
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

12:01.013 --> 12:02.932
<i>Starting him early, huh?
What's that?</i>

12:03.015 --> 12:05.684
Nothing.
Just, yeah, that's great.

12:05.768 --> 12:08.687
That'll be a great day.

12:08.771 --> 12:12.817
You know, we were hoping you
were going to make it down.

12:12.900 --> 12:17.405
To be honest,
it's tough for me tomorrow.

12:17.488 --> 12:20.282
Come on, Dad.
What do you got going on?

12:20.366 --> 12:23.494
<i>Just, you know, odds and ends.</i>

12:23.577 --> 12:25.913
Look, if it's
the church thing,

12:25.996 --> 12:27.790
you could just come
to the party afterwards.

12:27.873 --> 12:29.250
You don't even
have to wear a tie.

12:29.333 --> 12:30.668
That sweetens the deal.

12:34.463 --> 12:36.006
He coming?

12:36.090 --> 12:39.218
Yeah, Dad.
He's going to be there.

12:39.301 --> 12:41.679
<i>Mom's been married
to the guy for 20 years,</i>

12:41.762 --> 12:44.056
<i>you've said about as many words to him.
Yeah, well...</i>

12:44.140 --> 12:47.184
Look, like I said, son...

12:49.019 --> 12:51.355
things have been keeping me
a little busy up here.

12:53.399 --> 12:57.236
Right. Well...

12:57.319 --> 13:01.824
Won't bug you about it anymore.
You're not bugging me.

13:01.907 --> 13:04.410
No, you're not bugging me.

13:04.493 --> 13:07.371
Well, hey, maybe we'll drive
up sometime, surprise you.

13:07.455 --> 13:11.333
Yeah, well, better call first.

13:11.417 --> 13:13.377
Right.

13:13.461 --> 13:15.588
Okay. Well...

13:15.671 --> 13:17.006
<i>Leave you to it.</i>

13:19.758 --> 13:21.010
Goodbye, Dad.

13:21.969 --> 13:23.345
Bye, Chris.

13:26.348 --> 13:27.558
Bye.

13:37.735 --> 13:38.819
Ah...

13:41.030 --> 13:42.072
Fuck!

13:58.088 --> 13:59.381
Shit.

14:21.362 --> 14:23.280
Oh.

14:23.364 --> 14:25.574
God damn.

14:25.658 --> 14:26.951
<i>Oh, Shit.</i>

14:31.330 --> 14:32.498
Ah, shit.

14:48.097 --> 14:50.558
<i>You got engine trouble?</i>

14:53.185 --> 14:56.522
Long way from home, aren't you?
Well, that is the whole idea.

14:56.605 --> 14:58.983
I am on sabbatical
for my health.

15:01.193 --> 15:02.987
Yeah, well,
good luck on that.

15:03.070 --> 15:05.322
May I take a look? I got
it covered, thanks.

15:05.406 --> 15:06.782
It's no trouble.

15:06.865 --> 15:09.618
I just have
to tow it into town.

15:09.702 --> 15:11.704
But that is
30, 40 miles, no?

15:11.787 --> 15:15.040
Please allow me. I drove hack
in London for seven years

15:15.124 --> 15:18.460
and I had no choice but to become
expert on British automobiles.

15:18.544 --> 15:20.337
Really, I don't need any help.
Thank you.

15:20.421 --> 15:22.006
Okay. Okay.

15:28.012 --> 15:28.846
Hey.

15:30.514 --> 15:31.599
Sir.

15:33.475 --> 15:35.894
I just...

15:35.978 --> 15:39.690
I get this shooting
pain in my leg.

15:39.773 --> 15:41.108
Comes and goes.

15:41.191 --> 15:43.235
Always puts me in a bad mood.

15:49.950 --> 15:51.160
Try it.

15:55.789 --> 15:57.416
Ah, you got to be kidding me.
God damn it!

15:57.541 --> 16:01.003
Patience. I'm
trying to revive car.

16:01.086 --> 16:02.880
I don't want to have
to do the same for you.

16:02.963 --> 16:06.008
Well, I should've
just towed it in.

16:06.091 --> 16:07.468
Okay, once more,
if you please.

16:10.888 --> 16:12.056
Yeah.

16:12.848 --> 16:13.807
Ah.

16:14.683 --> 16:16.393
Well...

16:16.477 --> 16:19.396
You're a miracle worker.
Thank you.

16:21.690 --> 16:24.735
Body of Christ visited
in the filter housing.

16:24.818 --> 16:26.695
I don't like American cars,
very finicky.

16:26.779 --> 16:29.740
You have to be extremely
vigilant about maintenance.

16:29.823 --> 16:32.159
You have to listen
to every little thing.

16:32.242 --> 16:34.078
The shooting pain in my
leg is just killing me.

16:34.161 --> 16:36.580
I just got to get- Okay.
My sermon is over.

16:36.664 --> 16:39.083
Drug store will be closed
if I don't head out soon.

16:39.166 --> 16:41.001
Appreciate the help, mister?

16:41.085 --> 16:42.252
Emil

16:42.336 --> 16:44.797
Ben.
Benjamin Ford.

16:44.880 --> 16:46.382
Take it easy.

16:46.465 --> 16:47.341
You, too.

16:48.342 --> 16:49.760
Take it easy.

17:41.979 --> 17:44.064
You sure you're all
right out here?

17:44.148 --> 17:47.151
Where I come from, this is a
walk in the park. Where is that?

17:47.234 --> 17:50.446
I'm sure you would not
have heard of this place.

17:50.529 --> 17:52.740
I'm-
just leave it at that.

17:52.823 --> 17:54.575
Try me.

17:54.658 --> 17:56.744
Small village, Lukomir.
Oh, yeah, Bosnia.

17:56.827 --> 17:59.246
I was stationed in Bradina.

17:59.329 --> 18:02.416
Yeah. Well, then,
we are brothers.

18:02.499 --> 18:03.542
I don't know about that.

18:03.625 --> 18:05.836
I mean in arms.

18:05.919 --> 18:08.172
Let me shake your hand again.

18:08.255 --> 18:10.507
Yeah, small world.

18:10.591 --> 18:12.634
I have kept you long.
That's okay.

18:12.718 --> 18:15.179
The clock is ticking. It's too
dangerous to be driving anyway.

18:15.262 --> 18:17.222
I think I'm going to head back.
I'm going to ride it out.

18:17.306 --> 18:19.725
You're welcome
to join me if you want.

18:19.850 --> 18:22.853
But I would hate to be bother. I could
lie to you, say it's the Christian in me

18:22.936 --> 18:25.355
who wants you along, but truth
is if anything happens to you,

18:25.439 --> 18:27.816
it's going to come back
and bite me in the ass.

18:27.900 --> 18:29.818
There's a word for it.

18:29.902 --> 18:31.904
I believe it is karma.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.419
Few more minutes.

18:48.712 --> 18:50.255
Winchester, no?

18:50.339 --> 18:53.133
1873, the gun
that won the West.

18:53.217 --> 18:54.718
Yeah, you hunter like me.

18:54.802 --> 18:57.304
Yeah, every now and then.

18:57.387 --> 18:59.640
I don't use that.

18:59.723 --> 19:00.974
I use this.

19:04.561 --> 19:06.230
Evens the odds
a little bit.

19:06.313 --> 19:08.023
I wholeheartedly agree.

19:09.608 --> 19:11.819
You know,
I must confess,

19:11.902 --> 19:13.487
I did not come halfway
around the world

19:13.570 --> 19:15.989
just for mountain air.

19:16.073 --> 19:18.158
I came for trophy.
Oh, whitetail?

19:18.283 --> 19:23.205
Elk. Elk, they gave
you a tag, lucky dog.

19:23.288 --> 19:25.791
What'd you do, pull some strings
with Fish and Wildlife?

19:25.874 --> 19:29.920
No patience. You know, 18 months
ago I applied for license

19:30.003 --> 19:32.047
for five bull.

19:32.130 --> 19:35.008
Perhaps you come
with me tomorrow.

19:35.092 --> 19:36.844
No, really.

19:36.927 --> 19:40.430
The storm will be over
and the air will be clear

19:40.514 --> 19:42.558
and maybe, who knows,
you get lucky,

19:42.641 --> 19:44.810
you add another head
to your collection.

19:44.893 --> 19:46.728
Well, what are you using?
I use this.

19:46.812 --> 19:47.896
I'll show you.

19:54.278 --> 19:56.947
Here.
Jesus Christ, buddy.

19:57.030 --> 19:58.615
You fight
in the Indian Wars?

19:58.699 --> 20:01.910
No, this is the same bow
I used as a boy.

20:01.994 --> 20:06.039
You know, it's, gets
very clean strong draw.

20:07.749 --> 20:11.211
Not jerky like yours.
Well, mine won't snap.

20:11.295 --> 20:14.715
Any bow can snap.
That's fiberglass.

20:14.798 --> 20:16.842
I worked with fiberglass
in factory.

20:16.967 --> 20:20.637
That was after the war? No, before the war.
Old soldier like you.

20:20.721 --> 20:22.931
But sometimes
it is difficult

20:23.015 --> 20:25.976
to know when to leave
the battlefield, you know?

20:27.978 --> 20:30.147
You're talking
about the fiberglass.

20:30.230 --> 20:34.234
The tiny beer bubbles
find their way into the malt

20:34.318 --> 20:37.154
during
the manufacturing process.

20:37.237 --> 20:40.157
And then each time
you pull the string back,

20:40.240 --> 20:43.327
the fiberglass
weakens bit by bit.

20:43.410 --> 20:47.039
One day, you are tracking
your quarry through the grass,

20:47.122 --> 20:51.501
and the rocks, and the mud,
and the rain, and the snow,

20:51.585 --> 20:53.587
and finally
you see your prize bull

20:53.670 --> 20:56.089
right in the sights
and snap!

20:56.173 --> 20:57.466
It breaks.

21:00.469 --> 21:01.970
You're a weird duck.

21:02.971 --> 21:03.680
<i>Hmm.</i>

21:06.391 --> 21:08.268
What is this photographer?

21:08.352 --> 21:11.355
Oh, I did those.
Really?

21:11.438 --> 21:12.481
You're a photographer?

21:12.564 --> 21:14.608
Yeah.

21:14.691 --> 21:18.195
What is this one? Well, that's
the old church up in God's Peak.

21:18.278 --> 21:20.948
God's Peak.
Hmm.

21:21.031 --> 21:22.282
Reminds me of home.

21:24.493 --> 21:27.120
Oh, no, please, I'm fine.
Oh, you got to try it.

21:27.204 --> 21:31.041
I have more than I need,
and it doesn't keep real well.

21:31.124 --> 21:32.668
Or not.
It's a free country.

21:32.751 --> 21:33.543
Okay.

21:34.878 --> 21:36.254
If you insist.

21:53.522 --> 21:55.565
This is good. Good,huh?
Told you.

21:55.649 --> 21:57.484
It's delicious.

21:57.567 --> 22:01.071
Oh. It almost
slipped my mind.

22:01.154 --> 22:02.739
<i>I have something
to return the favor.</i>

22:10.789 --> 22:12.749
For the true hunter.

22:12.833 --> 22:15.419
It's too late for me now.
Oh, come on.

22:15.502 --> 22:18.880
You know, you did not
have aspirin today, okay?

22:18.964 --> 22:21.341
So, do not think
of it as a drink.

22:21.425 --> 22:25.178
Think of it
as pain killer.

22:25.262 --> 22:28.140
I always drink
with friend.

22:28.223 --> 22:29.599
Never alone.

22:29.683 --> 22:32.269
I have many rules,
most I break.

22:32.352 --> 22:34.312
But never that one.

22:34.396 --> 22:38.025
<i>So, Zivjeli.
Live long.</i>

22:38.108 --> 22:39.401
Zivjeli.

22:42.779 --> 22:44.948
<i>I'm felling you,
these women are beautiful.</i>

22:45.032 --> 22:48.201
They fuck all night,
I'm not kidding you.

22:48.285 --> 22:52.330
Okay, now, your turn.
You tell me stories.

22:52.456 --> 22:54.499
War stories. I want to hear this.
War stories?

22:54.583 --> 22:56.835
Yes. Most of those aren't true.

22:56.960 --> 23:01.131
Most, but some. Ones that are, why
would anyone want to talk about it?

23:01.214 --> 23:03.717
How else do you
keep the best life?

23:03.800 --> 23:05.677
The past is dead.
Let's keep it that way.

23:05.761 --> 23:09.222
No, see, now I see the
difference between you and me.

23:09.306 --> 23:11.892
You drink
to forget the past,

23:11.975 --> 23:14.186
I drink to remember.

23:14.269 --> 23:17.856
I don't remember much,
but this I do remember.

23:20.192 --> 23:23.403
The more booze
you brought over there,

23:23.487 --> 23:25.614
there was plenty of blood.

23:25.697 --> 23:26.907
To the war.

23:30.952 --> 23:32.621
Oh, come on, Benjamin.

23:32.704 --> 23:36.083
Is there not anything
you missed about the war?

23:36.166 --> 23:37.250
Only to not miss it.

23:37.334 --> 23:38.960
But why you say this?

23:39.044 --> 23:41.254
It was nothing but like
cakewalk for you, no?

23:41.338 --> 23:44.758
You don't have any idea what the
war was like for me, buddy.

23:46.968 --> 23:51.348
I misspoke. What I simply meant
is that most American soldiers

23:51.431 --> 23:54.434
did nothing more
but lob missiles into Bosnia

23:54.518 --> 23:57.604
from the safety of ships
floating in the Mediterranean.

23:57.687 --> 23:58.563
Most, not all.

24:06.029 --> 24:08.532
Three drinks.
Say again?

24:08.615 --> 24:11.827
My people say
we love Americans

24:11.910 --> 24:15.163
for three drinks,
but we've had five.

24:15.247 --> 24:17.749
And I still love you.

24:17.833 --> 24:19.292
Hey. Come on.

24:19.376 --> 24:22.087
<i>Let's have six.
Maybe seven.</i>

24:22.170 --> 24:24.673
Two more, we'll forget
we even had this conversation.

24:28.426 --> 24:32.472
